The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Opposition alleges phone tapping
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Opposition alleges phone tapping
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Naveen: In line of Opp. fire                                  
	Bhubaneswar, Dec. 8: The issue of alleged tapping of phones of a few Opposition leaders dominated proceedings of the unofficial Assembly session on the second day today.        
	Raising the issue through an adjournment motion, Opposition chief whip Prasad Harichandan, BJP legislature party leader K.V. Singhdeo and a few senior members of both the parties alleged that their telephones were being unethically and illegally tapped by the government.        
	Harichandan alleged that the telecommunication surveillance system, purchased by the state government under police modernisation scheme for keeping track on the movement of terrorists, were being misused against the governments political opponents.        
	Giving his ruling, Debi Prasanna Chand of Congress  who was presiding over the unofficial Assembly sitting  said if the government was resorting to such measures, it was illegal and unethical.         
	Demanding a white paper on the mining scam, leader of Opposition Bhupinder Singh alleged that the Naveen Patnaik government ran away from the Assembly by abruptly adjourning the winter session since a team from the Indian Bureau of Mines arrived in Joda and Barabil for probing into illegal mining.        
	Other major issues discussed today included failure of the government to publish the BPL list after seven years, bungling of PDS rice, distress sale of paddy and farmer suicides and failure of the government to utilise central funds.                                                                                                                                                          
